# Git Configuration

## .gitignore

```
# Environment variables
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# Backend
backend/venv/
backend/env/
backend/__pycache__/
backend/*.pyc
backend/.pytest_cache/
backend/.coverage
backend/htmlcov/
backend/scan_results.db
backend/scan_results.db-journal
backend/secrets/

# Frontend
frontend/node_modules/
frontend/build/
frontend/.DS_Store
frontend/.env.local
frontend/.env.development.local
frontend/.env.test.local
frontend/.env.production.local
frontend/npm-debug.log*
frontend/yarn-debug.log*
frontend/yarn-error.log*

# IDE
.vscode/
.idea/
*.sublime-project
*.sublime-workspace
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Logs
*.log
logs/
```

## Initial Commit

```bash
git init
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit: Email Threat Analyzer application"
git remote add origin <your-repo-url>
git push -u origin main
```

## Branch Strategy

For development:
```bash
# Create feature branch
git checkout -b feature/gmail-integration

# Commit changes
git add .
git commit -m "Add Gmail integration feature"

# Push to GitHub
git push origin feature/gmail-integration

# Create Pull Request on GitHub
```

## Deployment Branches

- `main` - Production ready code
- `develop` - Development branch
- `feature/*` - Feature branches
- `bugfix/*` - Bug fixes
- `hotfix/*` - Production hotfixes
